Description.Text: One of the historic *Seven Sisters* skyscrapers the stunning Hilton Moscow Leningradskaya hotel sits next to the Garden Ring. Only a short walk from the city*s main train station the hotel is located 25 kilometres from Sheremetyevo International Airport. Swim lengths in the heated indoor pool or work out in the 24-hour Fitness Centre. Visit the iconic Red Square nearby before savoring sumptuous Russian cuisine in the elegant Janus Restaurant.

Hilton Moscow Leningradskaya is centrally located. It is next to the Leningradskiy railway station - the main terminus for high-speed trains to St.Petersburg. The metro is served by the central line and the red line which is just three stops from Red Square so the hotel offers easy access to the city centre and environs.
The hotel is a landmark Stalinist-era tiered 'wedding-cake' style building, similar to several other properties throughout the city known as the Seven Sisters.

Janus Restaurant - Dine in the sophisticated Janus Restaurant at the Hilton Moscow Leningradskaya hotel and marvel at the hand-carved ceilings and elegantly dressed windows. Savor Russian specialties and choose a fine wine from the extensive selection to accompany your dish. Lobby Lounge - Enjoy lunch in the historical Lobby Lounge at the Hilton Moscow Leningradskaya hotel. Relax in the comfortable seating area and admire the Lounge*s magnificent marble columns and bronze statues as you treat yourself to a delicious cake or dessert.

Guests will be impressed the minute they walk into the hotel. The building was designed to reflect a medieval castle theme, so the walls are adorned with historic armour and decorated with dark wood. A large chandelier dominates the central space of the lobby. The lobby offers direct access to the restaurant and lobby bar areas.
